WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

03:16.562 --> 03:18.263
Hey.

03:18.264 --> 03:20.198
Simpson.

03:20.199 --> 03:22.100
I didn't think you'd come.

03:22.101 --> 03:23.969
We chewed the same sand.

03:23.970 --> 03:26.638
Yeah, I'm still pickin'
it outta my teeth.

03:26.639 --> 03:28.950
Shit, man.

03:31.711 --> 03:33.988
Long time.

03:34.246 --> 03:36.181
How ya doin', Smitty?

03:37.450 --> 03:40.418
I haven't heard that nickname
since Mission Sentinel.

03:40.419 --> 03:41.786
I'm doin' good.

03:41.787 --> 03:44.489
The German doctors
down in Landstuhl,

03:44.490 --> 03:46.324
they stitched me back
together pretty well.

03:46.325 --> 03:48.259
When'd you get outta that sandbox?

03:48.260 --> 03:49.728
Couple of months back.

03:49.729 --> 03:52.040
Doin' okay?

03:52.832 --> 03:55.300
They say I am.

03:55.301 --> 04:00.172
Hey, they broke me,
they gotta fix me.

04:01.507 --> 04:04.318
Welcome to the world.

04:14.987 --> 04:18.255
Listen, Smitty, I know this is not a good
time to be lookin' for a job. But if...

04:18.257 --> 04:20.829
I said I'm okay.

04:21.861 --> 04:26.164
I got a line on a job
over at Sembach Annex,

04:26.165 --> 04:28.609
training Army Snipers.

04:29.468 --> 04:34.077
You know what they say,
"Those who can't, teach."

04:34.607 --> 04:36.807
Well, the Army owes you that.

04:40.546 --> 04:43.281
It's my daughter Alex at school.

04:43.282 --> 04:44.683
I didn't know you had a kid.

04:44.684 --> 04:47.552
I got two, Alex and Lucy.

04:47.553 --> 04:51.457
Don't see much of 'em. Not anymore.

04:51.857 --> 04:53.963
Sorry.

04:54.226 --> 04:56.298
Yeah.

04:59.565 --> 05:02.701
You guys threw me under
the bus on Sentinel.

05:02.702 --> 05:06.776
We got sent on a bad
mission and people died.

05:07.006 --> 05:09.074
They hung that
friendly-fire shit on me.

05:09.075 --> 05:11.176
Your gun did it.

05:11.177 --> 05:13.078
I was ordered to fire.

05:13.079 --> 05:17.182
And I was ordered by the
Colonel to give those orders.

05:17.183 --> 05:19.653
Call it awash.

05:30.563 --> 05:32.397
What are we doin' here, Smitty?

05:32.398 --> 05:35.801
You got somethin' to say, say it.

05:38.738 --> 05:41.439
Do you think that
God will forgive us

05:41.440 --> 05:43.819
for all the shit that we've done?

05:45.444 --> 05:49.416
We did things right,
most of the time.

05:49.548 --> 05:52.291
We were drinkin' from
the devil's cup.

05:53.085 --> 05:55.658
That's just war.

05:56.021 --> 05:57.388
So that's it?

05:57.389 --> 05:59.257
That's it.

05:59.258 --> 06:01.092
Just like that.

06:01.093 --> 06:06.464
So fuck you and fuck the
Colonel, I did my job.

06:07.366 --> 06:09.370
And I did mine.

07:24.777 --> 07:27.312
Hey, did I tell ya?

07:27.313 --> 07:29.314
Getting my citizenship next month.

07:29.315 --> 07:32.024
- Finally came through, huh?
- Mmm-hmm.

07:32.451 --> 07:33.918
It pays to be a Marine.

07:33.919 --> 07:36.788
God, I can't wait to
have that blue passport.

07:36.789 --> 07:38.489
Well deserved.

07:38.490 --> 07:41.292
So, Corporal, you got an
interesting nickname.

07:41.293 --> 07:44.605
- Mango?
- Yeah, where'd it come from?

07:44.763 --> 07:47.932
My first live op, we
were in East Timor.

07:47.933 --> 07:51.636
Thirty days in the jungle,
short on food supply.

07:51.637 --> 07:54.472
Sol made my team a
mango-snake salad.

07:54.473 --> 07:56.875
What'd you season it with?

07:56.876 --> 07:58.776
Sea salt.

07:58.777 --> 08:00.211
Hmm.

08:00.212 --> 08:02.420
Sounds good right about now.

08:04.216 --> 08:07.357
- Movement, one o'clock.
- Range me.

08:10.122 --> 08:11.823
Thirteen hundred.

08:14.126 --> 08:15.560
On target.

08:15.561 --> 08:18.031
- Hold scope.
- Wind?

08:18.964 --> 08:21.399
It's comin' off the mountain
at our one o'clock,

08:21.400 --> 08:24.469
quarter value, push two
clicks to the right.

08:26.338 --> 08:27.639
Angle?

08:27.640 --> 08:31.248
Descending 18 degrees,
no adjustment.

08:32.578 --> 08:36.714
More Syrians coming into Turkey.
Who can blame 'em?

08:39.717 --> 08:41.961
Your move, Reese.

08:43.087 --> 08:45.399
White rook captures F five.

08:47.927 --> 08:49.093
Fuck.

08:49.094 --> 08:52.406
That's it, son. Check and mate.

08:52.765 --> 08:56.200
<i>NS-Two, NS-Two,
this is NS-One, over.</i>

08:56.201 --> 08:58.836
NS-One, this is NS-Two,
what's your traffic, over?

08:58.837 --> 09:01.572
NS-Two, please advise
on your sit rep, over.

09:01.573 --> 09:03.174
Livin' the dream, baby.

09:03.175 --> 09:05.009
How's your focus?

09:05.010 --> 09:10.325
Currently, I am focused
on cleaning my barrel.

09:10.549 --> 09:12.417
I can see your silhouette.

09:12.418 --> 09:15.264
<i>Get back in your hide.</i>

09:18.724 --> 09:20.258
Can I shake first?

09:20.259 --> 09:21.693
Oh, you got jokes?

09:21.694 --> 09:23.061
<i>Always.</i>

09:23.062 --> 09:26.364
Keeps me light, on the edge,
where I need to be.

09:26.365 --> 09:28.132
You need to be on your scope.

09:28.133 --> 09:31.235
<i>I know you're a member of the Green
Jackets Team back in the UK,</i>

09:31.236 --> 09:33.638
but sniping isn't just
about shooting straight,

09:33.639 --> 09:35.473
you also have to shoot first,

09:35.474 --> 09:37.041
<i>so get back on your rifle.</i>

09:37.042 --> 09:40.712
<i>Tell knucklehead riding shotgun
to put the chess set away.</i>

09:40.713 --> 09:42.380
Aye-aye.

09:48.587 --> 09:52.058
Got something. Could
be our guy. 12 o'clock.

09:52.958 --> 09:54.625
This party's startin'.

09:54.626 --> 09:57.128
NS-Two, put your dick
away and lock it up.

09:57.129 --> 09:59.838
Time to go to work.

10:12.144 --> 10:15.279
Vehicle, belt-fed AK.
They're coming heavy.

10:15.280 --> 10:17.659
Call it out.

10:25.657 --> 10:28.826
Target on ground.
Head-wrap, sackcloth.

10:28.827 --> 10:30.294
He's a real charmer.

10:30.295 --> 10:32.333
Hey!

10:33.098 --> 10:35.443
Do the math.

10:36.602 --> 10:38.302
970 meters.

10:38.303 --> 10:40.805
Wind, one-half value.

10:40.806 --> 10:45.745
Angle, 13 degrees descending.
No adjustment.

10:47.946 --> 10:49.514
On target.

10:49.515 --> 10:51.519
Fire when ready.

10:54.353 --> 10:56.220
Refugees are blocking my shot.

10:56.221 --> 10:59.123
NS-Two, do you have a clean
shot to the Tango, over?

10:59.124 --> 11:00.491
Give me a sec.

11:00.492 --> 11:02.326
Go two up.

11:02.327 --> 11:04.562
This is a senior Taliban.

11:04.563 --> 11:07.331
If you have a clean shot,
send the mail now.

11:07.332 --> 11:09.575
Roger that, over.

11:10.636 --> 11:12.503
Put some lead on this guy, Reese.

11:12.504 --> 11:14.906
<i>Do it now!</i>

11:16.208 --> 11:18.416
Hey! Hey!

11:21.180 --> 11:23.081
- Miss.
- Ready for a gunfight?

11:23.082 --> 11:26.155
- Thought you'd never ask.
- Go to guns.

11:50.342 --> 11:51.909
Hit.

11:51.910 --> 11:53.244
Give me a shot.

12:08.627 --> 12:12.633
NS-Two, you have two hostile
technicals approaching your position.

12:16.468 --> 12:19.109
Fuck me! We're takin' heavy fire!

12:24.476 --> 12:26.616
Man down! Man down!

12:27.379 --> 12:29.314
Position to lead truck.

12:31.416 --> 12:35.286
816 meters and closing,
25 miles an hour.

12:35.287 --> 12:37.689
Two-mil lead.

12:49.568 --> 12:51.970
Beckett, I need some help!

12:54.773 --> 12:57.241
Large rock, 750 meters.

12:57.242 --> 12:58.643
Two guys on foot.

13:06.985 --> 13:10.889
Guy with the AK, on the
ground, 800 meters.

13:16.962 --> 13:20.001
- Hostile threat down.
- Where's the target?

13:25.003 --> 13:27.171
Heading south, fast.

13:27.172 --> 13:29.415
Range me.

13:33.378 --> 13:34.779
Range is long gone.

13:34.780 --> 13:36.852
Call it in.

13:40.352 --> 13:42.019
Let's pack it up.

13:42.020 --> 13:44.092
Yeah.

13:45.290 --> 13:48.793
Hog's Den, Hog's Den,
this is North Star One.

13:48.794 --> 13:52.129
Hostile threat down.
Ready for evacuation, over.

13:52.130 --> 13:56.443
<i>Roger that, NS-One, move to
extraction point LZ-Cobra.</i>

13:57.069 --> 13:59.971
Hold your position.

15:22.721 --> 15:25.156
What the hell happened, Gunny?

15:25.157 --> 15:27.758
You'll read about it
in the report, sir.

15:27.759 --> 15:28.893
Reese?

15:28.894 --> 15:31.162
Yahoo, no discipline.

15:31.163 --> 15:33.631
That's why you're here,
to train these yahoos.

15:33.632 --> 15:35.399
Look around you.

15:35.400 --> 15:37.935
This is a work in progress,
not even the fucking paint's dry.

15:37.936 --> 15:39.570
We had him.

15:39.571 --> 15:41.839
Should've been clean, done.

15:41.840 --> 15:43.810
It was that bad?

15:45.410 --> 15:47.411
Worse.

15:47.412 --> 15:49.416
Reese got his spotter killed.

15:50.916 --> 15:54.160
Well, let me buy you a drink.
We'll talk it through.

15:55.120 --> 15:56.587
I want out, Major.

15:56.588 --> 15:58.489
What are you saying?

15:58.490 --> 16:01.158
You sent us into a country we
weren't even supposed to be in,

16:01.159 --> 16:03.427
with a team that wasn't
qualified for the job.

16:03.428 --> 16:05.529
We lost one today.
We'll get him next time.

16:05.530 --> 16:10.501
No, I had five kills today and we
were only sent out for one target.

16:10.502 --> 16:12.370
It's tough work.

16:12.371 --> 16:15.840
Not really, that's what bothers me.

16:15.841 --> 16:19.043
It was easy, five shots, five kills.

16:19.044 --> 16:21.846
I was on the scope, correcting
for wind and velocity,

16:21.847 --> 16:23.547
doing the trig work in
my head, on the fly.

16:23.548 --> 16:25.216
Yeah, it's just math.

16:25.217 --> 16:28.018
No, everything was easy.

16:28.019 --> 16:30.287
Second nature?

16:30.288 --> 16:32.289
Yeah.

16:32.290 --> 16:33.991
That's the goal.

16:33.992 --> 16:36.927
Congratulations, you're a sniper.

16:36.928 --> 16:40.531
It's what we do. Black on black.

16:40.532 --> 16:42.843
It's ugly stuff.

16:46.772 --> 16:49.674
You're not the first sniper
to question his destiny.

16:51.276 --> 16:53.553
We all do.

16:54.513 --> 16:57.120
You think I like to kill?

17:03.955 --> 17:06.198
I'm done.

17:06.724 --> 17:09.160
You're assigned to a
Multi-National Task Force

17:09.161 --> 17:12.329
authorized to carry weapons
in a foreign country!

17:12.329 --> 17:14.732
You can't just quit!

17:16.067 --> 17:18.913
You're a natural, kid.

17:19.871 --> 17:22.579
It's in your blood.

18:44.556 --> 18:46.624
You're 10 minutes late.

18:46.625 --> 18:51.228
Major, you still don't know when
you're talking to a superior?

18:51.229 --> 18:55.008
It's along time since we've had
a come-to-Jesus face to face.

18:55.800 --> 18:57.804
I'm not here.

18:59.804 --> 19:02.907
The rest of us are in the shit and
you're living the life out here.

19:02.908 --> 19:07.756
Way off the grid, out of the
grind, right where I need to be.

19:08.146 --> 19:12.858
You must rate some serious
juice with the brass stateside.

19:13.485 --> 19:16.763
Pete Steffen, you remember him?

19:18.490 --> 19:20.591
Yeah. Reasonably good man.

19:20.592 --> 19:23.165
Got shot in Berlin, two days ago.

19:23.595 --> 19:25.029
Shame.

19:25.030 --> 19:28.132
It would be a shame
if it was just Steffen.

19:28.133 --> 19:30.341
Hopkins and Carswell.

19:30.535 --> 19:32.102
Dead?

19:32.103 --> 19:35.539
Hopkins got popped nine
days ago in South Florida.

19:35.540 --> 19:37.007
Carswell?

19:37.008 --> 19:40.115
Medulla shot, two
days back in London.

19:40.645 --> 19:46.283
Shots were from 1,500 meters
with a high-caliber bullet.

19:46.284 --> 19:48.552
- How high?
- Fifty.

19:48.553 --> 19:52.022
That's not a just a kill,
that's a statement.

19:52.023 --> 19:55.960
It was a home-made bullet with
its own calculated spindrift.

19:55.961 --> 19:57.161
Conditions?

19:57.162 --> 20:01.131
Hopkins' shot required an
adjustment for extreme wind.

20:01.132 --> 20:03.636
- From 1,500 meters?
- Mmm-hmm.

20:04.235 --> 20:07.071
This guy's a serious motherfucker.

20:07.072 --> 20:10.174
Let's get the hell outta
of here. You hungry?

20:16.414 --> 20:18.015
Best octopus in the world.

20:19.985 --> 20:22.387
You brought me here
because you think I did it?

20:23.154 --> 20:24.355
Why would you say that?

20:24.356 --> 20:27.424
There are only a handful of
guys can make those shots,

20:27.425 --> 20:29.395
and I'm one of them.

20:30.228 --> 20:34.109
If I thought you did it,
we wouldn't be talking.

20:34.432 --> 20:36.066
Fair enough.

20:36.067 --> 20:37.868
We have three men dead out of five

20:37.869 --> 20:40.671
who were put together for a
particular mission in Afghanistan,

20:40.672 --> 20:43.540
a mission you turned down.

20:43.541 --> 20:45.042
Didn't see any upside in it.

20:45.043 --> 20:48.012
Everyone involved got a high-paying
job with the corporation

20:48.013 --> 20:49.213
when they got back home.

20:49.214 --> 20:51.749
With all due respect, sir, the men
that get those high-paying jobs

20:51.750 --> 20:55.290
end up about six feet lower
than I care to park my desk.

20:56.021 --> 20:57.388
Who do you think did it?

20:57.389 --> 20:59.768
Ideas or actionable intel?

21:01.760 --> 21:03.394
What's your gut say?

21:03.395 --> 21:06.196
Simpson. Got the raw talent.

21:06.197 --> 21:09.566
He just got back from Afghanistan
a couple months ago.

21:09.567 --> 21:11.802
Spent time in the psych
ward at Landstuhl.

21:11.803 --> 21:13.637
He's been in the shit too long.

21:13.638 --> 21:16.707
We think he's somewhere in Syria,
tracking one of our members.

21:16.708 --> 21:17.808
Shope?

21:17.809 --> 21:20.644
And we think your boy Beckett
might also be on his list.

21:20.645 --> 21:22.413
Why would he want Brandon?

21:22.414 --> 21:26.488
Because last night there
was a fourth killing.

21:41.666 --> 21:42.933
Thomas Beckett?

21:42.934 --> 21:44.869
He was taken out in Rome.

21:47.672 --> 21:51.212
<i>He was the best shooter I ever knew.</i>

21:52.577 --> 21:55.320
<i>Fucker could thread a needle.</i>

21:56.481 --> 21:58.655
So what are you gonna do about it?

21:59.484 --> 22:02.660
Find Simpson, shut him down.

22:09.861 --> 22:13.530
There's an ax coming through
your door, Colonel.

22:13.531 --> 22:15.666
And this island's not
so far off the grid.

22:15.667 --> 22:18.335
That's why I've got you.

22:18.336 --> 22:21.273
This is all the Intel we have.

22:21.673 --> 22:23.507
Sir.

22:23.508 --> 22:25.546
Hey.

22:27.178 --> 22:30.058
They still calling you Bullet-Face?

23:08.987 --> 23:12.766
So I hear you're lookin'
for a transfer?

23:12.991 --> 23:14.858
Word travels fast.

23:14.859 --> 23:16.393
When were you gonna tell me?

23:17.595 --> 23:21.165
- Sanaa, I...
- No, look... Fine, it's fine.

23:21.166 --> 23:23.170
Just thought we were friends.

23:23.201 --> 23:25.136
We are.

23:25.370 --> 23:28.539
- Doesn't feel like it sometimes.
- It does to me.

23:28.540 --> 23:32.109
It's so much easier for you guys,

23:32.110 --> 23:35.456
especially you with your legacy.

23:35.547 --> 23:37.517
My legacy?

23:40.752 --> 23:42.995
Wanna know why I became a sniper?

23:43.555 --> 23:45.627
Yeah.

23:48.026 --> 23:49.961
Republic of the Congo.

23:50.195 --> 23:52.696
A sniper took out my entire squad,

23:52.697 --> 23:55.099
missed killing me by
less than an inch.

23:56.234 --> 23:58.435
I don't believe in misses.

23:58.436 --> 24:00.537
The bullet either
wants you or doesn't.

24:00.538 --> 24:02.473
Hmm.

24:03.908 --> 24:05.409
Hey, Beckett!

24:05.410 --> 24:07.411
Bullet-Face is sending me home.

24:07.412 --> 24:09.947
You rat-fucked me.

24:09.948 --> 24:13.250
I did you a favor, Reese. Go home.

24:13.251 --> 24:15.919
The Green Jackets will be happy
to have their shooter back.

24:15.920 --> 24:18.697
We've got some business
to finish first.

24:22.126 --> 24:23.927
You really wanna do this?

24:23.928 --> 24:25.429
Oh, yeah.

24:30.802 --> 24:33.375
Fucking Beckett!

24:44.782 --> 24:46.850
So what was that all about?

24:46.851 --> 24:51.622
Just a couple of guys who kill for
a living getting into a bar fight.

24:51.623 --> 24:54.658
What are you doing here, Brandon?

24:54.659 --> 24:57.232
Chasin' a ghost.

24:57.462 --> 24:59.796
Thomas Beckett?

24:59.797 --> 25:03.200
Walkin' in the shadow of a giant.

25:04.469 --> 25:07.042
He's just a man, Brandon.

25:10.708 --> 25:15.055
I'll tell you a story about
a girl and her father.

25:15.346 --> 25:19.716
They lived in this small town
in the south of Lebanon.

25:20.184 --> 25:22.686
He was the mayor.

25:22.687 --> 25:24.454
He was working with the
police to try to stop

25:24.455 --> 25:27.357
local farmers from
growing heroin poppy.

25:30.194 --> 25:32.903
One day the girl came
home from school.

25:34.399 --> 25:39.042
She found her father's severed
head on the front steps.

25:39.737 --> 25:44.744
The police who had been hired to
protect him, assassinated him.

25:45.677 --> 25:47.744
I'm sorry.

25:47.745 --> 25:52.092
My mom picked up our lives
and moved us to Chicago.

25:52.817 --> 25:55.162
Never looked back.

25:55.553 --> 25:57.321
And you?

25:57.322 --> 25:58.956
I joined the Corps.

25:58.957 --> 26:01.625
Actually where I
realized I could shoot.

26:01.626 --> 26:03.827
Which brings me here,

26:03.828 --> 26:06.530
back in the Middle East,
shooting long-guns

26:06.531 --> 26:10.033
with you at the command
of Major Bidwell.

26:10.034 --> 26:13.039
I actually learned a lot from him.

26:15.340 --> 26:20.043
He taught me that no matter
what country you're in,

26:20.044 --> 26:23.982
you don't really know
who the bad guys are.

26:24.248 --> 26:27.217
So you find a shooter who you trust

26:27.218 --> 26:30.120
and join forces with him.

26:46.037 --> 26:47.972
Gunny?

26:49.273 --> 26:52.585
Get dressed, I need a minute.

27:00.585 --> 27:02.953
Major?

27:02.954 --> 27:06.590
I'm not good at small talking
over the facts of things,

27:06.591 --> 27:09.027
so I'm just gonna
come out and say it.

27:09.260 --> 27:13.835
A U.S. sniper went rogue and
killed several military officers.

27:14.265 --> 27:17.270
One of those men was your father.

27:23.074 --> 27:25.476
My father?

27:25.576 --> 27:28.012
I'm sorry, kid.

27:29.881 --> 27:31.816
How?

27:32.717 --> 27:34.051
Who?

27:34.052 --> 27:36.022
That's need to know.

27:37.655 --> 27:43.197
I know you never knew him and
maybe it doesn't matter to you,

27:44.662 --> 27:47.371
but he was the best
shooter I ever knew.

27:48.399 --> 27:50.676
He would've been proud of you.

27:52.770 --> 27:54.808
Is that it?

27:54.939 --> 27:59.377
No, I'm gonna take a small
team and tie this thing off.

28:00.411 --> 28:04.414
I can't take you with me
because the Colonel says so.

28:04.415 --> 28:06.483
Besides, you wouldn't
know how to keep

28:06.484 --> 28:09.419
on the trigger without
making it personal.

28:09.420 --> 28:11.621
This isn't personal for you?

28:11.622 --> 28:13.557
Yes, it is.

28:13.658 --> 28:16.401
But I know how to make it a job.

28:16.627 --> 28:20.098
Our training teaches us
not to personalize killing.

28:20.598 --> 28:22.533
